Exception Handling:
Response contains 3 parts:
Status code: 3digit numeric value send by the server along with the response to the client.
HTTP return code likje 200 OK, 500 Interanal_error
Header: Additional info(Optional)
Body: data need to be sent in response.

1. 1XX(100- 199)--->Informative(rearly used)
2. 2XX(200- 299)---> Syccess
     201--->Created(POST)
     200---> Success(GET AND POST)
    202---> ACCEPETED
      204---> No content
3. 3XX(300- 399---> Redirection
      301---> Serource been moved permanently to another url
       302----> temporarly moved to diff url.
4. 4XX(400-499)----> client side error ex. tipo error
       400--->Bad request
       401---> unauthorized
        403---> forbidden---> when we try to do something when only admin has an access.
        404---> not found
       405----> Method not allowed
        422----> Un-processableentity(bs validation)
        429--->Too many requests
5. 5XX (500-599)---> Server side error
       500--->Internal server error(heneric error)
     501---> Not implemented(it's still developing)
        502---> bad gateway

200 OK: request got successfull

In SB we can use ResponseEntity<T> to create Response and in this T re represents the type of the Body.

Exception Handling:
Exception handling in Spring Boot is a mechanism to handle runtime errors gracefully and return meaningful HTTP responses instead of server crash messages (500 stack traces).

‚ÄúWe prefer RuntimeException because it avoids unnecessary boilerplate, supports clean layered architecture, and works well with global exception handling.‚Äù

1. Custom exception handling
Custom exception handling means:
Creating your own exception classes
Throwing them when business rules fail
Handling them centrally using Global Exception Handler
Returning meaningful, controlled error responses
üëâ Instead of ugly runtime errors, your API behaves professionally.


2. Error response model
An Error Response Model is a POJO that defines how errors are sent to the client in a structured JSON format instead of plain text.

3. Global exception handling(RestControllerAdvice, @Exceptionhandler)
In Spring Boot, global exception handling means handling exceptions at one central place instead of writing try‚Äìcatch blocks in every controller.

4. validation exception handling
Validation exception handling in Spring Boot captures MethodArgumentNotValidException and ConstraintViolationException to return structured error responses when request data violates validation rules.



